Philepitta is a genus of bird in the family Philepittidae. Established by Isidore Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire in 1838, the genus contains the following species:
The genus name Philepitta is a combination of the French name phil√©don, for the friarbirds of the family Meliphagidae and pitta, for the birds of the genus "pitta".Philepitta is now the type-genus of a new bird family, the Philepittidae, into which the Asites of Madagascar have been placed.